%N A240199 Area under the path specified by n-th composition.
%C A240199 Compositions are in the order specified in A066099.
%C A240199 Path has run lengths given by the specified composition followed by its reversal.
%C A240199 Can be considered a table with row lengths A011782 (2^(n-1)).
%C A240199 Maximum in row n is n^2, for [n]; minimum is 2*n-1 for [1,n-1].
%e A240199 Row 5 of A066099 is [2,1]. The path generated by [2,1,1,2] is:
%e A240199 __
%e A240199   |_
%e A240199     |
%e A240199 ____|
%e A240199 The area under the path is 8, so a(5) = 8.
%o A240199 (PARI) A066099row(n) = {local(v=vector(n),j=0,k=0);
%o A240199    while(n>0,k++; if(n%2==1,v[j++]=k;k=0);n\=2);
%o A240199    vector(j,i,v[j-i+1])} \\ row n of A066099.
%o A240199 patharea(v) = {local(m=#v,n=sum(k=1,m,v[k]),w,r=0);
%o A240199    w=vector(2*m,k,if(k<=m,v[k],v[2*m+1-k]));
%o A240199    forstep(k=1,2*m,2,r+=w[k]*n;n-=w[k+1]);
%o A240199    r}
%o A240199 a(n) = patharea(A066099row(n)) \\ _Franklin T. Adams-Watters_, Apr 02 2014
